<div class="container" style="max-width: 980px;">
    <div class="mt-4 mb-4">
        <h1 class="display-4" style="font-weight: 600;">Smart Foot Traffic Monitor System</h1>
        <p class="lead mb-0">
            A monitoring and analytics dashboard for understanding pedestrian, cyclist, and vehicle movement patterns
            in the Footscray CBD to Victoria University corridor.
        </p>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">Project Overview</h3>
        <p>
            Smart Foot Traffic Monitor System is a capstone solution designed to help stakeholders understand movement
            behaviour across Footscray. It combines <strong>real-time updates</strong> and <strong>historical analysis</strong>
            to reveal patterns, identify peak periods, and support planning decisions using clear, interactive visualisations.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">Purpose</h3>
        <p>
            This system supports evidence-based decision making for councils, transport planners, and local businesses by
            transforming sensor data into actionable insights. It enables users to explore traffic intensity by location and time,
            compare trends across different movement types, and export filtered datasets for reporting and further analysis.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">Key Capabilities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Interactive heatmaps</strong> showing zone-based movement intensity across selected time ranges.</li>
            <li><strong>Advanced filtering</strong> by time/date range, zone, movement type, direction, season, and other contextual indicators.</li>
            <li><strong>Contextual insights</strong> by relating traffic patterns to public transport proximity and VU schedule timing.</li>
            <li><strong>Export tools</strong> for generating filtered outputs and reports in <strong>CSV</strong> and <strong>PDF</strong> formats.</li>
            <li><strong>Fast dashboard exploration</strong> with paged results to keep the interface responsive and user-friendly.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">Stakeholders</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local councils:</strong> planning, safety improvements, and infrastructure investment.</li>
            <li><strong>Transport providers:</strong> peak demand analysis and service planning.</li>
            <li><strong>Victoria University:</strong> access patterns, class scheduling impact, and campus movement insights.</li>
            <li><strong>Local businesses:</strong> understanding foot traffic trends and optimising trading periods.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">Non-Functional Requirements</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Performance:</strong> UI responses targeted under <strong>3 seconds</strong> per interaction.</li>
                    <li><strong>Update cycle:</strong> new data processed approximately every <strong>15 minutes</strong>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> designed to support at least <strong>10×</strong> dataset growth.</li>
                    <li><strong>Availability:</strong> targeted uptime of <strong>99.9%</strong> for reliable access.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Security:</strong> TLS in transit and encrypted storage where applicable (AES-256 aligned).</li>
                    <li><strong>Access control:</strong> role-based access control (RBAC) with optional 2FA support.</li>
                    <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> WCAG 2.1-aligned UI practices (labels, contrast, keyboard use).</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit & retention:</strong> activity logging and GDPR-style data retention considerations.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-weight: 600;">High-Level Architecture</h3>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Ingestion:</strong> sensor feeds (real-time) and CSV imports (historical datasets).</li>
            <li><strong>Processing:</strong> validation, cleaning, enrichment, and aggregation (time buckets / zones).</li>
            <li><strong>Storage:</strong> structured database optimised for fast filtering, querying, and reporting.</li>
            <li><strong>Visualisation:</strong> heatmaps, dashboards, and export generation for stakeholder reporting.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
            <strong>USP:</strong> Hyper-local, easy-to-read visual insights with contextual signals (seasonal patterns,
            transport proximity, and VU schedule alignment).
        </div>
    </section>

